float, string, Core::Fields::ScalarField, array<float>, array<long>, array<bool>

Generates the colours based on the colour curve or, if
[color is profile] is selected, based on the profile curve. Lerps from center to edge.
Generates [amount] points in a sphere of [radius] with uniform probibility.
Because each sphere is calculated at the origin, the distance from the center is just the length of the position.  The offset is applied later.
This calculates the distribution options and multiplies them by the point positions, then the offset per point is applied.
Calculates the new distance to the local center. This is used for colour and normals.

this is a modification to the original paper. instead of using the
same grid everywhere, we use a randomly generated grid. this does
not lead to problems for us because we even check for collision of
items that were assigned to the same bucket. we might get a
problem where too many items get removed, but in practice it doesn't
seem to be a big issue
